    "about": "ADS Maritime Holding Plc is a shipping investment company incorporated in Cyprus in 2018 and listed on Euronext Growth Oslo. Formerly known as ADS Crude Carriers Plc (renamed December 2020), the company is managed by Arendals Dampskibsselskab AS, a well-established Norwegian shipping investor. Its strategy focuses on counter-cyclical investments in vessels bought at prices discounted to new-building parity — particularly tankers and bulkers — as well as long-term secured cashflow projects. Current holdings include shuttle tankers through AET Sea Shuttle AS, a joint venture with AET providing DP2 Offshore Loading Shuttle Tankers on long-term charter to Equinor in the North Sea. Some vessels operate on LNG dual-fuel solutions.",
